[SN]TITLE[SN]
Belfast shooting was 'reckless madness', police say

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have said the shooting of a police officer in north Belfast was 'reckless madness'.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
23 January 2017 Last updated at 00:14 GMT
The attack happened near a petrol station on the Crumlin Road on Sunday night. The officer is in a stable condition in hospital.
Assistant Chief Constable Mark Hamilton said their main line of inquiry is "violent dissident republicans".
